      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation performed and dominant inputs identified via sensitivity ranking at Gradation 5.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed over three input parameters (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity) with 500 samples; 95th-percentile prediction interval on NIH reported. However, sensitivity analysis to rank the relative contribution of each input to output variance has not been conducted — the dominant drivers remain uncharacterized. The team notes an intention to extend this work with variance-based sensitivity indices in a follow-on study. Achieved level 2 due to absence of sensitivity ranking.",
